    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix trx_lms_set_gains multi-channel support and error handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `trx_lms_set_gains` function in LMSSDR driver was not properly handling multi-channel configurations and had inconsistent error reporting. This fix addresses these issues to ensure proper gain setting across all configured channels.\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/LMSSDR/lms_lib.cpp`: \n  - Modified `trx_lms_set_gains` to iterate through all RX/TX channels instead of only channel 0\n  - Added proper error checking for LMS API calls with detailed error reporting\n  - Improved handling of RX gain limit violations (70dB) by setting to maximum rather than failing\n  - Enhanced error messages to include channel-specific information\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen configuring LimeSDR devices with multiple channels, only channel 0 gains were being set while other channels retained default values. Additionally, when RX gain exceeded 70dB, the function would return error code but still attempt to set the excessive gain value, leading to inconsistent behavior.\n\nUsers may observe unexpected signal levels on channels beyond the first, or inconsistent gain settings when operating near hardware limits.\n"
}